The paper discusses on-disk data processing, which is closely related to database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). It also touches upon architecture (cs.AR) and operating systems (cs.OS) as they play a crucial role in implementing ODDP. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Solid State Drives (SSDs) for ODDP, which falls under the category of storage systems (cs.SI).
